Practical Assignment: Data Foundations for Machine Learning
Title
Analysis of Factors Influencing Annual Salaries in the Technology Sector
1. Dataset Description and Collection Method

This study investigates salary patterns within the technology sector by analyzing how key job-related factors influence annual income levels.
The dataset was manually compiled by reviewing 54 active job postings from reputable professional platforms, including LinkedIn, Indeed, and selected local company career websites.

Each posting was examined individually, and relevant attributes—such as required experience, education level, work arrangement, company size, and listed salary—were systematically recorded in a spreadsheet.

To ensure consistency:

Salary ranges were converted to a single midpoint value.

Hourly wages were transformed into annual salaries using a full-time assumption of 40 hours per week and 52 weeks per year.

This dataset was created specifically for academic purposes and was not obtained from any pre-existing public dataset, ensuring originality and relevance to the assignment.

2. Features (X) and Target Label (y)

To support meaningful machine learning analysis, the following variables were collected.

Input Features (X)
Feature Name	Type	Description
Years of Experience	Numerical	Total years of relevant professional experience required
Education Level	Categorical	Highest degree required (High School, Bachelor’s, Master’s, PhD)
Remote Status	Categorical	Work arrangement: Remote, Hybrid, or On-site
Company Size	Categorical	Organization scale: Small (<50), Medium (50–500), Large (500+)
Programming Skills Count	Numerical	Number of technical skills or technologies mentioned in the posting
Output Variable (Label y)

Annual Salary (USD) – Represents total yearly compensation.
When a salary range was provided, the midpoint value was recorded.

This structure makes the dataset highly suitable for supervised learning, particularly regression modeling.

3. Dataset Structure

Total Samples (Rows): 54

Total Variables (Columns): 6

5 input features

1 target label

Sample Data (First 5 Records)
Experience (Years)	Education	Remote	Company Size	Tech Count	Salary (USD)
3	Bachelor’s	Remote	Medium	4	85,000
0	Bachelor’s	On-site	Large	2	55,000
7	Master’s	Hybrid	Small	5	110,000
5	Unknown	Remote	Medium	3	95,000
